{"type":"message","id":"dbff00cf","parentId":"83639529","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:11:16.574Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kccf900dxg7n_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5795\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3830\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 011015 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariants vs variants across pulse logs and predict subsequent pulse content.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"good-reef","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5795\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3830\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 011015 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariants vs variants across pulse logs and predict subsequent pulse content.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774329076537}}
{"type":"message","id":"c36fdc29","parentId":"dbff00cf","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:11:16.583Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kccf900dxg7n_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 010714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a pending TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n3. The next action should implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n4. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe last pulse was `pulse_2026-03-24 010505.md` and no mutations were applied.\r\n\r\nI should implement the TIC classifier. This is the next concrete action that advances the Phase 1 advancement goal.\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Reads the last 20 pulse log files\r\n2. Analyzes for invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content\r\n4. Reports accuracy metrics\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script for this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across recent pulse logs to test if causal structure can be discovered through compression.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `temporal_invariance_classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that reads the last 20 pulse logs, identifies invariant (persistent across sessions) vs variant (session-specific) patterns, and measures classification accuracy against success criteria (>70% invariant/variant, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env pwsh\r\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$LogCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    $logs = @()\r\n    Get-ChildItem \"$LogDir/pulse_*.md\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | \r\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\r\n        Select-Object -First $LogCount |\r\n        ForEach-Object { \r\n            $logs += @{\r\n                Path = $_.FullName\r\n                Name = $_.Name\r\n                Content = Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw\r\n                Time = $_.LastWriteTime\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    return $logs\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract key-value patterns (invariant candidates)\r\nfunction Get-KeyPatterns {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    $patterns = @{}\r\n    # Extract headers, goals, key metrics\r\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^## (.+)$') { \r\n        $patterns['headers'] = $matches[1] \r\n    }\r\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^\\- \\[ \\] (.+)$') { \r\n        $patterns['pending'] = $matches[1] \r\n    }\r\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^\\- \\[x\\] (.+)$') { \r\n        $patterns['complete'] = $matches[1] \r\n    }\r\n    if ($Content -match '(?m)^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}') { \r\n        $patterns['has_dates'] = $true \r\n    }\r\n    return $patterns\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate invariant score between two logs\r\nfunction Get-InvariantScore {\r\n    param([string]$Log1, [string]$Log2)\r\n    $score = 0\r\n    $total = 0\r\n    \r\n    # Header matching (high weight)\r\n    if ($Log1 -match '(?m)^# .+$' -and $Log2 -match '(?m)^# .+$') {\r\n        $total += 2\r\n        if ($matches[0] -eq $Log1.Substring($Log1.IndexOf('#'), $Log1.IndexOf(\"`n\") - $Log1.IndexOf('#'))) {\r\n            $score += 2\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Pending items (medium weight)\r\n    $pending1 = [regex]::Matches($Log1, '(?m)^\\- \\[ \\] (.+)$')\r\n    $pending2 = [regex]::Matches($Log2, '(?m)^\\- \\[ \\] (.+)$')\r\n    $total += [Math]::Max($pending1.Count, $pending2.Count)\r\n    foreach ($p in $pending1) {\r\n        if ($Log2.Contains($p.Groups[1].Value)) { $score++ }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Phase markers\r\n    $phases = @('Phase 0', 'Phase 1', 'Phase 2')\r\n    foreach ($phase in $phases) {\r\n        $total++\r\n        if ($Log1.Contains($phase) -and $Log2.Contains($phase)) { $score++ }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return if ($total -gt 0) { $score / $total } else { 0 }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Main execution\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n$logs = Get-PulseLogs\r\nWrite-Host \"Loaded $($logs.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\nif ($logs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Insufficient logs for analysis\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Build invariant/variant classification\r\n$invariantScore = 0\r\n$variantScore = 0\r\n$predictionScore = 0\r\n\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $logs.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n    $current = $logs[$i]\r\n    $next = $logs[$i + 1]\r\n    \r\n    $score = Get-InvariantScore $current.Content $next.Content\r\n    \r\n   \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:07:43\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774329076572}}
